          <div class="col-sm-9">

              <div id="accordion">

                <div id="list-item-1" style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
                  <p style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 20px;">General</p>
                  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 5px;">
                    <div class="card-header" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne" id="One">
                      <h5 class="mb-0">
                        <button class="btn btn-link faq-link" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                          <span class="fa fa-plus" style="margin-right: 8px;"></span>
                          What can I do with the application in general?
                        </button>
                      </h5>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="One" data-parent="#accordion">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        The DEWI - Direct Extreme Weather Information application is a Web Platform for the representation of social media data in dependency to actual extreme weather events.
                        The main part of the platform is a map on which the user can choose an area of interest.
                        In this area the current extreme weather events and the most recent geotagged twitter posts are shown.
                        The user can click on one of the twitter posts, which are shown as markers in the map and
                        the twitter post fitting to the chosen marker will be highlighted in an overview. This works the other way around.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 5px;">
                    <div class="card-header" id="Two" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                      <h5 class="mb-0">
                        <button class="btn btn-link faq-link" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                          <span class="fa fa-plus" style="margin-right: 8px;"></span>
                          What is the scope of the application?
                        </button>
                      </h5>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="Two" data-parent="#accordion">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        The platform can be used especially by civil protection experts to deliver them additional information in extreme weather situations.
                        The information will support them to manage a possible disaster situation faster and more efficient
                        because they can recognize the strength of the weather event and send corresponding to their recognitions the best help to this location.
                        Therefore, timestamps are provided to all information to get a better overview of the most recent data.
                        Furthermore,the source of data is available, so that the experts can proof if its reliable.
                        This way information concerning the weather event are much earlier available than if journalists
                        and emergency crews first must reach the event, what is the main advantage of the platform
                        compared to the usual procedure.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 5px;">
                    <div class="card-header" id="Three" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                      <h5 class="mb-0">
                        <button class="btn btn-link faq-link" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                          <span class="fa fa-plus" style="margin-right: 8px;"></span>
                          Who are the developers of the application?
                        </button>
                      </h5>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="Three" data-parent="#accordion">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        The application was developed by students during the <a href="https://studium.uni-muenster.de/qisserver/rds?state=verpublish&status=init&vmfile=no&publishid=303090&moduleCall=webInfo&publishConfFile=webInfo&publishSubDir=veranstaltung" target="_blank">Geosoftware II</a>
                        course in the bachelor program Geoinformatics in the winter term 2019/ 2020 at the Institute for Geoinformatics (<a href="https://www.uni-muenster.de/Geoinformatics/en/" target="_blank">ifgi</a>) of the University of MÃ¼nster (<a href="https://www.uni-muenster.de/en/" target="_blank">WWU</a>).
                        The source code an further information are available on <a href="https://github.com/tnier01/DEWI_Geosoft2_WS19-20_huef_jaku_nier_nisk_sten/" target="_blank">github</a>.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 5px;">
                    <div class="card-header" id="Three" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                      <h5 class="mb-0">
                        <button class="btn btn-link faq-link" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                          <span class="fa fa-plus" style="margin-right: 8px;"></span>
                          Why does the application use cookies?
                        </button>
                      </h5>
                    </div>
                    <div id="collapseFour" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="Four" data-parent="#accordion">
                      <div class="card-body">
                        The application requires cookies to keep the data up-to-date in real time without requiring user interaction.
                        Furthermore cookies are used to save user specific default values or rather basic settings.
                        Cookies are not passed on to third parties and are not used for other purposes.
                        The user agrees with this circumstances by starting to use the application.
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 5px;">
                    <div class="card-header" id="Seventeen" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseSeventeen" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                      <h5 class="mb-0">
                        <button class="btn btn-link faq-link" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                          <span class="fa fa-plus" style="margin-right: 8px;"></span>
